ric data\nacquired under different soil moisture levels, resulting in an average\npercentage relative discrepancy of about 3% in bare soil condition and of 4%\nduring the vegetated period. The temporal evolution of corrected soil water\ncontent values exhibits a dynamic range coherent with the soil hydraulic\nproperties in terms of wilting point, field capacity and saturation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Sep 2018 15:57:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-11"}
